# Philosophy Research API Keys
# To set a key here, uncomment its line and add your value after the "=".
# Keys exported in your shell environment work as-is and can stay commented;
# a value set in this file takes priority over the environment.

# Semantic Scholar API key (optional but recommended for higher rate limits)
# Get one at: https://www.semanticscholar.org/product/api
# S2_API_KEY=

# Email for CrossRef API (required for paper verification)
# Used to identify your requests per CrossRef's polite pool
# CROSSREF_MAILTO=

# Email for OpenAlex API (recommended for higher rate limits)
# Used to access the polite pool with faster responses
# OPENALEX_EMAIL=

# Brave Search API key (required for SEP/PhilPapers discovery)
# Get one at: https://brave.com/search/api/
# BRAVE_API_KEY=

# CORE API key (optional; improves CORE full-text discovery)
# Get one at: https://core.ac.uk/services/api
# CORE_API_KEY=

# Advanced: override the User-Agent sent when fetching SEP/IEP/NDPR pages
# directly. Leave unset to use PhilLit's honest default bot UA; set only if a
# downstream packaging must identify itself distinctly (e.g. with a mailto).
# PHILLIT_FETCH_USER_AGENT=
